John McCain was nominated as the Republican candidate, and he selected Sarah Palin as his running mate. The two candidates engaged in three presidential debates in September and October 2008.[198] On November 4, Obama won the presidency with 365 electoral votes to 173 received by McCain.[199] Obama won 52.9 percent of the popular vote to McCain's 45.7 percent.[200] He became the first African American to be elected president.[201] Obama delivered his victory speech before hundreds of thousands of supporters in Chicago's Grant Park.[202]
